        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "perf(test): fix explicit-file Vitest wrapper hangs",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Route simple explicit-file `scripts/run-vitest.mjs` invocations through the existing `scripts/test-projects.mjs` project router so single-file agent proof does not load the full root Vitest project matrix.\n- Keep direct Vitest behavior for explicit config/root/project, watch/dev mode, and separate option-value invocations where project-router parsing could change semantics.\n- Add the missing active-memory and Codex extension project-router kinds so delegated explicit extension tests run real shards instead of being skipped.\n\n## Timing Proof\n\n| Case | Command | Result |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Before this patch, temporary copy of `HEAD:scripts/run-vitest.mjs` with a 5s idle watchdog | `OPENCLAW_VITEST_NO_OUTPUT_TIMEOUT_MS=5000 node scripts/.run-vitest-before.$PID.mjs test/scripts/dependency-guard-workflow.test.ts` | No Vitest output before watchdog; SIGTERM at 5s, forced SIGKILL after another 5s; `/usr/bin/time -p` reported `real 13.92`, `user 13.02`, `sys 0.85`. |\n| After this patch | `/usr/bin/time -p node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/dependency-guard-workflow.test.ts` | Selected `test/vitest/vitest.tooling.config.ts`, 7 tests passed; `[test] passed ... in 2.36s`; `/usr/bin/time -p` reported `real 2.48`, `user 2.01`, `sys 0.29`. |\n| Reported Minimax example after this patch | `/usr/bin/time -p node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/minimax/oauth.test.ts` | Selected `test/vitest/vitest.extension-providers.config.ts`, 4 tests passed; `[test] passed ... in 4.26s`; `/usr/bin/time -p` reported `real 4.31`, `user 3.97`, `sys 1.11`. |\n| Reported changelog attribution example after this patch | `/usr/bin/time -p node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/check-changelog-attributions.test.ts` | Selected `test/vitest/vitest.tooling.config.ts`, 8 tests passed; `[test] passed ... in 2.67s`; `/usr/bin/time -p` reported `real 2.72`, `user 2.33`, `sys 0.58`. |\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/run-vitest.test.ts` - 31 tests passed.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/test-projects.test.ts` - 103 tests passed.\n- `/usr/bin/time -p node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/dependency-guard-workflow.test.ts` - 7 tests passed; `real 2.48`.\n- `/usr/bin/time -p node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/minimax/oauth.test.ts` - 4 tests passed; `real 4.31`.\n- `/usr/bin/time -p node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/check-changelog-attributions.test.ts` - 8 tests passed; `real 2.72`.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/index.test.ts` - 7 tests passed.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/active-memory/index.test.ts` - 127 tests passed.\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 scripts/run-vitest.mjs scripts/test-projects.test-support.mjs test/scripts/run-vitest.test.ts test/scripts/test-projects.test.ts` - passed.\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` - clean, no accepted/actionable findings.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Bare explicit-file `scripts/run-vitest.mjs <file>` agent runs no longer stall in the root multi-project Vitest startup path for the reported examples; they select the narrow project shard and run the requested file.\n\nReal environment tested: Local macOS source checkout on branch `vitest-hanging`, Node 24.16.0, pnpm 11.2.2.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: See the Verification section above.\n\nEvidence after fix: The three reported examples completed and printed their selected shard. `test/scripts/dependency-guard-workflow.test.ts` improved from forced-kill at `real 13.92` with a 5s watchdog to a successful run at `real 2.48`.\n\nObserved result after fix: The wrapper delegates simple explicit-file invocations to `test-projects.mjs`, preserves direct Vitest behavior for option-heavy/watch/config/root/project cases, and routes active-memory/Codex extension targets to real extension configs.\n\nWhat was not tested: Full Vitest suite, full `pnpm check`, remote Testbox/Crabbox proof.\n",
